1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:06,507
<i>At the end of the last century,
on northern Europe's coasts,</i>

2
00:00:06,507 --> 00:00:08,884
<i>lived men who feared
neither God nor the law.</i>

3
00:00:09,051 --> 00:00:13,722
<i>They lured ships towards the rocks
where they were smashed to pieces.</i>

4
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:20,229
These <i>men then plundered the wrecks.
They were called wreckers.</i>

5
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:23,774
<i>The captain is their leader.
He is a brute.</i>

6
00:00:24,024 --> 00:00:26,735
<i>His strength gives him
power over his henchmen.</i>

7
00:00:26,735 --> 00:00:30,739
<i>He has committed so many crimes
that he's become almost mad.</i>

8
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:34,618
<i>Villagers say he is haunted
by the ghosts of his victims.</i>

9
00:00:35,327 --> 00:00:38,038
<i>His madness makes him
dangerous and unpredictable.</i>

10
00:00:39,248 --> 00:00:43,961
<i>Le Bosco, cursed by all navies,
the bad seed of any crew.</i>

11
00:00:44,295 --> 00:00:49,341
<i>He landed there dead-drunk from a foreign
ship one night with his bag on his shoulder.</i>

12
00:00:50,134 --> 00:00:53,304
<i>He follows the captain,
but this sailor,</i>

13
00:00:53,304 --> 00:00:56,140
<i>never without his knife,
dislikes taking orders.</i>

14
00:00:56,891 --> 00:01:00,895
<i>He bides his time like a vulture.
He is false and crafty.</i>

15
00:01:01,604 --> 00:01:04,231
<i>Paul.
He, too, is a former sailor.</i>

16
00:01:04,732 --> 00:01:08,736
<i>He suffers the captain's orders,
but grovels to Le Bosco.</i>

17
00:01:09,361 --> 00:01:11,280
<i>He will be on the winner's side.</i>

18
00:01:11,572 --> 00:01:16,660
<i>He is cruel and cowardly and has
a worse temper than the others.</i>

19
00:01:17,036 --> 00:01:21,290
<i>He is the strongest, because each of
the three thinks he is on his side.</i>

20
00:01:22,249 --> 00:01:24,919
<i>Tina, the wrecker.
The angel of the accursed.</i>

21
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,295
<i>Wild and perverted.</i>

22
00:01:26,503 --> 00:01:29,590
<i>This cruel animal is always
ready to snap up the</i>

23
00:01:29,590 --> 00:01:32,593
<i>innocent who come too close
to her she-wolf jaws.</i>

24
00:01:33,135 --> 00:01:34,511
<i>She will show no pity.</i>

25
00:01:34,511 --> 00:01:38,432
<i>It's a game for her to plunder wrecks
and kill survivors.</i>

26
00:01:39,058 --> 00:01:41,185
<i>More than one dead man,
his throat cut,</i>

27
00:01:41,185 --> 00:01:47,608
<i>takes with him the image of her
magnificently shameless naked body.</i>

28
00:06:45,155 --> 00:06:46,240
Help.

29
00:06:47,824 --> 00:06:49,034
Help.

30
00:06:54,831 --> 00:06:55,791
Help.

31
00:07:37,958 --> 00:07:38,959
Help us!

32
00:07:55,517 --> 00:07:56,560
Help!

33
00:17:41,394 --> 00:17:42,896
Something wrong, Captain?

34
00:17:47,317 --> 00:17:48,902
Leave me alone.

35
00:19:14,362 --> 00:19:15,363
Look!

36
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:19,284
Hey, clear off, you drunk.
- Get lost.

37
00:19:51,774 --> 00:19:54,319
Now what's the matter?
Have you gone mad?

38
00:19:55,820 --> 00:19:59,866
There. A moment ago.
Didn't you see anything?

39
00:20:00,783 --> 00:20:02,660
Here? I'm the only one here.

40
00:20:24,724 --> 00:20:27,185
Are you afraid of ghosts, Captain?

41
00:20:40,531 --> 00:20:43,826
I thought I saw something.
It's nothing. It's nothing.

42
00:20:48,748 --> 00:20:49,874
It's nothing.

43
00:21:03,471 --> 00:21:05,515
Sounds like he saw a ghost.

44
00:21:07,225 --> 00:21:09,268
Maybe there was a ghost.

45
00:21:09,685 --> 00:21:10,645
Just for him?

46
00:21:11,646 --> 00:21:14,690
Yes. Just for him.

47
00:21:53,062 --> 00:21:54,063
Help!

48
00:22:30,516 --> 00:22:31,976
Bring us some drinks.

49
00:22:36,647 --> 00:22:38,691
A ship has been wrecked on the rocks.

50
00:22:39,025 --> 00:22:40,151
A ship? When?

51
00:22:42,028 --> 00:22:43,362
Only a few hours ago.

52
00:22:44,530 --> 00:22:45,781
How do you know?

53
00:22:47,158 --> 00:22:48,117
Were you there?

54
00:22:49,202 --> 00:22:51,579
To cause a shipwreck?

55
00:22:52,121 --> 00:22:54,582
O" Purpose?

56
00:22:55,166 --> 00:22:56,334
Of course it was on purpose.

57
00:22:56,334 --> 00:22:57,376
Shut up!

58
00:22:58,127 --> 00:23:00,463
You know very well there
are no wreckers anymore.

59
00:23:01,923 --> 00:23:03,090
Who knows?

60
00:23:03,758 --> 00:23:05,384
The tide may have
washed up the bodies.

61
00:23:06,010 --> 00:23:08,804
I asked you if you were there.

62
00:23:10,431 --> 00:23:15,520
What about you? Were you there?
- Me? No.

63
00:23:17,396 --> 00:23:18,523
I was here!

64
00:23:19,398 --> 00:23:21,817
So, why have you got
blood on your shirt?

65
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:30,034
You're crazy.
There's nothing there.

66
00:23:33,204 --> 00:23:35,164
God curse the wreckers!

67
00:23:43,589 --> 00:23:45,424
The sun is rising over the shore!

68
00:23:46,717 --> 00:23:48,344
A sad and gray day!

69
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:51,097
The tide is out!

70
00:23:53,057 --> 00:23:55,226
I can see two small figures.

71
00:23:56,602 --> 00:23:57,853
They are getting up!

72
00:23:59,855 --> 00:24:02,149
They start walking.
- That's enough!

73
00:24:03,901 --> 00:24:05,152
Shut up!

74
00:24:05,945 --> 00:24:07,029
They are still weak.

75
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:11,617
They support each other
and stagger forward.

76
00:24:13,035 --> 00:24:17,540
Be warned! If they discover the
secret of this cursed village,

77
00:24:18,249 --> 00:24:20,418
nothing will stop
them from taking revenge.

78
00:24:57,246 --> 00:25:00,833
Let the ghosts come.
I'm not afraid of anyone.

79
00:25:01,375 --> 00:25:02,918
Let them come and see the captain!

80
00:25:09,425 --> 00:25:13,971
God or devil.
Come and have your throats slit.

81
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:16,265
Come on, then.

82
00:25:17,725 --> 00:25:19,101
Come on, ghosts.

83
00:25:21,270 --> 00:25:24,273
Come on, phantoms. Come on, demons.

84
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:26,484
Come back and see the captain.

85
00:25:27,026 --> 00:25:27,985
I challenge you.

86
00:25:29,654 --> 00:25:33,199
You died tonight.
I will kill you again!

87
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:36,702
We have to shut him up or
he'll tell them everything.

88
00:25:36,952 --> 00:25:38,037
He's drunk.

89
00:25:38,621 --> 00:25:41,957
I saw your heads smashed
against the rocks!

90
00:26:37,346 --> 00:26:39,056
What the hell is going on'?

91
00:26:45,479 --> 00:26:46,731
I don't want any trouble here.

92
00:26:47,189 --> 00:26:50,568
It's morning. We're closing now.
Finish your drinks and go.

93
